  "text": "Motorola is announcing the Edge 60 Fusion on April 2, and ahead of the unveiling we have some more leaked renders of it to look at today. These seem quite official, and are showcasing the device in all four colors in which it will be sold, according to the source. Motorola Edge 60 Fusion leaked renders While we don't yet know what these colors' names will be, don't be surprised if one or more of them use Pantone color names, thanks to Motorola's ongoing partnership with Pantone. Motorola Edge 60 Fusion leaked renders As you can see, the frame is color matched to the rear of the phone in all four versions, and there are four camera circles placed onto a raised island. Motorola Edge 60 Fusion leaked renders The Motorola badge is smack dab in the middle, and the screen is curved on the sides, meeting the frame as the back does. According to past leaks, rumors, and teasers, the Motorola Edge 60 Fusion will be the first smartphone to use MediaTek's new Dimensity 7400 chipset. Motorola Edge 60 Fusion leaked renders The phone should have a 50 MP main camera using Sony's Lytia LYT-700 sensor, a 13 MP ultrawide, a 32 MP selfie camera, and a 5,500 mAh battery with support for 68W wired charging. In Europe, the Edge 60 Fusion will allegedly cost €350 with 8GB of RAM and 256GB of storage, thus being the cheapest model in the upcoming Edge 60 line. Source",
